<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,366,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Forewing upperside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[450,563,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[157,1438,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[148,1439,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Talbotia naganum aurelia Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—HT♂: central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; E–F—PT♀ same location as the male. Talbotia naganum pamsi Vitalis de Salvaza, C–D—♂: northern Vietnam, Lang Son province, Mau Son; G–H—♀: northern Vietnam, Vinh Phuc province, Tam Dao N.P." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556608/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Figure 4E</figureCitation>
) Ground colour of the forewing varies from uniformly white to uniformly very pale yellowish unequally dusted with black scales; pattern includes a thick black border around the wing perimeter with small gap in cell Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[441,457,457,471]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">1b</subScript>
, which includes a black oval spot; discal cell densely covered by black scales or it is fully black; discocellular veins covered by distinct black spot and thick black band connects discal cell with black border in cell M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[330,338,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">3</subScript>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,588,510,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Forewing underside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[602,715,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[157,1438,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[148,1439,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Talbotia naganum aurelia Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—HT♂: central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; E–F—PT♀ same location as the male. Talbotia naganum pamsi Vitalis de Salvaza, C–D—♂: northern Vietnam, Lang Son province, Mau Son; G–H—♀: northern Vietnam, Vinh Phuc province, Tam Dao N.P." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556608/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Figure 4F</figureCitation>
) Ground colour of the white, densely dusted with blackish scales especially within discal cell; yellowish ochreous border spread from mid costa to mid termen becoming broader at the apical area; black band within discal cell curve behind discocellular vein and broadened at termen within cell M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[176,184,637,651]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">3</subScript>
; another black band extends within cells 2A and Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[770,786,637,651]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">1b</subScript>
from the basal area to the termen where it terminates as a large oval spot in cell Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[430,446,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">1b</subScript>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[460,703,654,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Hindwing upperside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[717,834,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[157,1438,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[148,1439,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Talbotia naganum aurelia Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—HT♂: central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; E–F—PT♀ same location as the male. Talbotia naganum pamsi Vitalis de Salvaza, C–D—♂: northern Vietnam, Lang Son province, Mau Son; G–H—♀: northern Vietnam, Vinh Phuc province, Tam Dao N.P." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556608/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Figure 4E</figureCitation>
). Ground colour of hindwing varies from pale creamy (specimens of dsf) to yellowish; series of marginal blackish triangle spots from vein Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1135,1151,709,723]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">1b</subScript>
to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1213,1221,709,723]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">2</subScript>
and spot in cell Rs usually weakly developed; in some specimens of dsf these spots fully disappeared; basal area dusted with black scales. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[235,481,762,788]" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Hindwing underside</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[498,616,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[157,1438,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[148,1439,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Talbotia naganum aurelia Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—HT♂: central Vietnam, Gia Lai province, Kon Ka Kinh N.P.; E–F—PT♀ same location as the male. Talbotia naganum pamsi Vitalis de Salvaza, C–D—♂: northern Vietnam, Lang Son province, Mau Son; G–H—♀: northern Vietnam, Vinh Phuc province, Tam Dao N.P." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556608/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="493">Figure 4F</figureCitation>
). Ground colour of the hindwing uniformly intensive yellow with light golden tinge; fringe is white.
</paragraph>
